$$
\begin{gathered}
N=n \times N_A=0.5 \times 6.022 \times 10^{23} \\
N=3.011 \times 10^{23} \text { atoms }
\end{gathered}
$$

An empirical formula represents the **simplest whole-number ratio** of atoms ($
\text{C}_1\text{H}_2\text{O}_1$
) in a compound, while a molecular formula specifies the **exact number** of atoms of each element in a molecule ($
\text{C}_6\text{H}_{12}\text{O}_6$
).
